definition[0]: in a less important position than someone else
example[2]: These aims were subordinate to the main aims of the mission.
definition[2]: someone who has a lower position and less authority than someone else in an organization
definition[3]: to put someone or something in a less important position
example[3]: Why subordinate your wishes to those of your family?
definition[4]: less important or powerful than something or someone
example[4]: a subordinate role on the committee
example[5]: a commission that is subordinate to the Security Council
example[6]: Supervisors are regularly evaluated by their subordinates.
